text: I haven't played this game so I'm not sure if it's any good, but Tetris is usually a safe bet. I was looking for some Masato Kouda music (Devil May Cry, Wild Arms 4-5...) and stumbled upon this soundtrack. It sounds completely different from what I expected since this is Disney related, but different in a good way. This plays against Pete, which is the game's "final boss". Quite a dark theme, but no surprise coming from Kouda.
author: SupraDarky

author: Eric C.

text: I've always felt this one wasn't as awesome as Big Bad Wolf's funky disco theme! Personally it's the best song of the game! Mickey's, Donald's, and Goofy's themes are also pretty nice! As for gameplay, it's basically Tetris, but with a lot of competitive mechanics. For example, if you do combos or several row-clearings with one piece, you can make the other player have bigger and more complicated Tetris pieces to screw him over. Definitely one of the best Tetris games I have played!
